		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">18.201</ph> Contingency operation.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <ol id="d1116e13" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1130e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            Contingency operation is defined in <xref href="FAR-i1125359.dita#i1125359"
                        base="i1125359"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">2.101</xref>.</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1130e29" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            Micro-purchase threshold. The threshold increases when the head of the agency determines the supplies or services are to be used to support a contingency operation. (See <xref href="FAR-i1125359.dita#i1125359"
                        base="i1125359"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">2.101</xref> and <xref href="FAR-i1111870.dita#i1111870"
                        base="i1111870"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">13.201</xref>(g).)</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1130e44" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            Simplified acquisition threshold. The threshold increases when the head of the agency determines the supplies or services are to be used to support a contingency operation. (See <xref href="FAR-i1125359.dita#i1125359"
                        base="i1125359"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">2.101</xref>.)</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1130e56" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            
						            <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i "/>
						            <xref href="https://www.gsa.gov/forms-library/us-government-purchase-order-invoice-voucher"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">SF 44</xref>, Purchase Order-Invoice-Voucher. The normal threshold for the use of the <xref href="https://www.gsa.gov/forms-library/us-government-purchase-order-invoice-voucher"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">SF 44</xref> is at or below the micro-purchase threshold. Agencies may, however, establish higher dollar limitations for purchases made to support a contingency operation. (See <xref href="FAR-i1111753.dita#i1111753"
                        base="i1111753"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">13.306</xref>.)</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1130e76" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(e)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            
						            <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Simplified procedures for certain commercial items</i>. The threshold limits authorized for use of this authority may be increased for acquisitions to support a contingency operation. (See <xref href="FAR-i1111260.dita#i1111260"
                        base="i1111260"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">13.500</xref>(c).)</p>
				        </li>
